news.title: Dalmia Bharat's net profit up 137% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Dalmia Bharat's consolidated total income stood at Rs 3,390 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 22.60 per cent from Rs 2,765 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Colorado considers using public land for affordable housing
news.para: Until last month, the 26-year-old, his wife and their two small children were squeezed into one bedroom in a three-bedroom house that held nine other tenants - the best they could afford because of bloated housing prices fueled in part by sky-high land costs.

news.title: Arihant Superstructures' net profit up 72.28% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Arihant Superstructures' consolidated total revenue stood at Rs 115.20 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 34.63 per cent from Rs 85.57 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Home prices in Toronto fall in January, down 22% from peak
news.para: The average price of a GTA home fell to C$1.04 million ($780,957) in January, down 1.2% from December and down 16.4% from a year ago. Prices were about 22% below February's peak.

news.title: Berhampur civic body threatens allotment cancellation if house not self-occupied
news.para: The caution came after it found out that around 35% beneficiaries were not living in their houses allotted under Rajiv Awas Yojana (RAY) at Jharana Nagar, when a team paid a visit on Thursday afternoon.

news.title: Consumer panel orders SBI General Insurance to pay Rs 30 lakh claim for building slab collapse
news.para: ​The commission ordered SBI General Insurance Company Ltd to pay the claim amount within 45 days of the order, failing which 9 per cent per annum will have to be paid till the realisation.

news.title: NGT orders probe into hill cutting, tree-felling for real estate project in Himachal Pradesh
news.para: Parasher alleged that Indu Walia, also a local resident and the director of Group Colonisers Private Ltd, was selling plots after mass scale felling of trees and levelling of hill tops on her land measuring 7.5 hectares in Malahat village near Una town.

news.title: Gurugram: No land acquisition yet, water infra a worry, Sohna societies rely on tankers
news.para: DTCP recently asked HSVP to acquire land for setting up water boosting stations for supply in these colonies and societies, prompting the development authority to constitute a team to finalise a six-acre land for developing the crucial infrastructure.

news.title: Indore civic body's new portal to approve maps of up to 3,000 sq ft area in 48 hours
news.para: According to mayor Pushyamitra Bhargava, IMC’s building permission cell has started approving maps through an online portal to construct houses in the legal colonies that will be operated without human interaction and will save time and energy of the applicants.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government adds 55 villages to YEIDA territory
news.para: The total number of notified villages in the YEIDA has now gone up to 1,242. The authority area has been extended to the Delhi-Howrah railway route, Dedicated Freight Corridor (DFC) and new Noida.

news.title: Centre links grants for 'B' civic bodies to property tax growth
news.para: The government has sent a letter to the Nashik Municipal Corporation in this connection, stating that it would get the grant under the Finance Commission only if it registered 25% growth in the property collection in the 2023-24 financial year, as compared to that in the current financial year (2022-23).

news.title: Sand and gravel to be available at pit head price of Rs 5.50 per cubic feet in Punjab
news.para: In August 2022, the state government had fixed the pit head selling price of sand and gravel at the rate of Rs 9 per cubic feet including loading charges.

news.title: Secunderabad cantonment board razes 50 illegal buildings in two weeks
news.para: In the past two weeks, over 50 such illegal structures have been razed in all the eight civilian wards by officials of engineering wing of the Secunderabad Cantonment Board (SCB).

news.title: Kolkata: New UAA property tax system for Sector V to be launched on April 1
news.para: Officials said that the West Bengal Valuation Board, which had earlier come up with a draft scheme on the UAA system of tax collection for Sector V, has finalised the proposed structure, based on which NDITA will start collecting tax.

news.title: Reforms panel proposes 1% sports cess on property tax in Bengaluru
news.para: The three-member panel, led by former chief secretary TM Vijayabhaskar, made these recommendations in its fourth and fifth edition of the KARC report which was submitted on Friday to chief minister Basavaraj Bommai.
